# Chatbot Development Patterns

## Architecture Awareness

The chatbot is a Streamlit app (`rag-chatbot`) that talks to LlamaStack (`lsd-rag`).
It has two modes (Direct, Agent) with different APIs and prompt patterns. Changes to
one mode should not break the other.

## Key Constraints

### tool_choice = "required" in agent mode
`agent.py` sets `tool_choice="required"` when tools are present. This is intentional ŌĆö
Granite 8B frequently skips tools when set to "auto". Do not change without extensive
testing across all 4 agentic test scenarios.

### max_output_tokens = 512
The 16K context window fills up fast with MCP/file_search results (12-16K). A larger
`max_output_tokens` causes vLLM to reject requests. Only increase if the model's
`max-model-len` is also increased.

### System prompt brevity
Granite 8B narrates verbose prompts instead of acting on them. Keep the agent system
prompt action-oriented and under ~100 words. Use positive framing ("You MUST use tools")
instead of negative ("Do NOT explain your reasoning").

## Testing Cycle

After code changes:
```
oc start-build rag-chatbot -n private-ai --follow
oc rollout restart deployment/rag-chatbot -n private-ai
oc rollout status deployment/rag-chatbot -n private-ai
```

After env-only changes (e.g., `RAG_QUESTION_SUGGESTIONS`):
```
oc rollout restart deployment/rag-chatbot -n private-ai
```

Always test in both Direct and Agent modes after changes.

## Container Image Guidelines

The chatbot's `Containerfile` follows [OCP 4.20 container image guidelines](https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/openshift_container_platform/4.20/html/images/creating-images):
- Base: `registry.access.redhat.com/ubi9/python-312:latest` (Red Hat UBI9, not Docker Hub)
- Runs as `USER 1001` (OCP random UID compatible)
- Single process (`streamlit run`)
- No `hostPath`, no privileged capabilities

When modifying the `Containerfile`:
- Do NOT switch to a Docker Hub base image ŌĆö use Red Hat UBI or RHOAI images
- Do NOT remove `USER 1001` ŌĆö OpenShift requires non-root by default
- Group `RUN` commands to minimize layers (per [RHOAI custom image guidelines](https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/red_hat_openshift_ai_self-managed/3.3/html/managing_openshift_ai/creating-custom-workbench-images))
- Pin package versions in pip install commands for reproducibility

## What NOT to Change Without Full Testing

- `tool_choice` value in `agent.py`
- Guardrails orchestrator endpoint or API version in `guardrails.py`
- `RAG_QUESTION_SUGGESTIONS` JSON key names (must match vector store names)
- The `LlamaStackApi` singleton pattern in `api.py`

